[1] Hungary (southeast), suspected
Date: Mon, 22 Jan 2007
From: Mary Marshall <tropical.forestry@btinternet.com> [edited]
Source: Reuters [edited]
<http://today.reuters.com/news/articlenews.aspx?type=globalNews&storyid=2007-01-22T182904Z_01_L22847398_RTRUKOC_0_US-BIRDFLU-HUNGARY.xml&src=rss>

Five geese which died in southeastern Hungary are
being tested for suspected bird flu, an official
of the farm ministry was quoted as saying on Monday [22 Jan 2007].
The dead birds, which are being tested in
Budapest, come from a large farm in southeastern
Csongrad county where about 40 geese fell sick
and some died, Farming Ministry Secretary of
State Fulop Benedek told the national news agency MTI.
Veterinarians who saw the birds said the suspicion of bird flu was justified.
The Hungarian authorities established a protected
zone around the farm and informed international
organizations concerned, Benedek said. Hungary
culled a million birds after the highly
infectious H5N1 strain of bird flu hit domestic poultry last summer.
--
