[3] China (Hong Kong SAR): wild birds
Date: Mon, 22 Jan 2007
From: Mark Liao <markliaohk@gmail.com>
Source: Hong Kong SAR Government Press Release [edited]
<http://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/200701/22/P200701220215.htm>

The Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation
Department (AFCD) said today (22 Jan 2007) that
the Japanese White-eye, the House Crow and the
White-backed Munia found earlier were confirmed
to be H5N1 positive after a series of laboratory tests.
The carcass of the Japanese White-eye [_Zosterops
japonicus_, picture at
<http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Image:Zosterops_japonicus_01.jpg>]
was collected by AFCD staff on 15 Jan 2007 on
Convair Drive, San Po Kong. The House Crow and
the White-backed Munia [_Lonchura striata_,
picture at
<http://pragtfinker.com/images/fugle/asien/lonchura_striata.png>]
were found on 16 Jan 2007 from Lai On Estate,
Sham Shui Po and at 101 ï¿½ 109 Boundary Street, Mong Kok, respectively.
A department spokesman reminded the public to observe good personal hygiene.
"They should avoid personal contact with wild
birds and live poultry and clean their hands
thoroughly after coming into contact with them," he said.
--
Mark Liao
<markliaohk@gmail.com>
